'''Hannes Piterson Delcroix''' (born 28 February 1999) is a Haitian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] or [[left-back]] for [[Swiss Super League]] club [[FC Lugano|Lugano]] and the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Club career==
Delcroix was born in [[Petite Rivière de l'Artibonite]], Haiti, and at a young age moved to [[Kalmthout]], in Belgium.

===Anderlecht===
Delcroix joined the youth academy of [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.anderlecht-online.be/nl/article/150330|title=Anderlecht Online – Maak kennis met Hannes Delcroix (05 jan 17)|website=www.anderlecht-online.be}}</ref> Delcroix signed his first professional contract with Anderlecht on 25 January 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Hannes-delcroix-passe-professionnel-a-anderlecht/771995|title=Hannes Delcroix passe professionnel à Anderlecht|last=Rédaction|publisher=}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Anderlecht in a 5–2 [[Belgian First Division A]] win over [[K.V. Oostende|Oostende]] on 5 August 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ca.soccerway.com/matches/2018/08/05/belgium/pro-league/royal-sporting-club-anderlecht/kv-oostende/2794768/|title=Anderlecht vs. KV Oostende – 5 August 2018 – Soccerway|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

===RKC (loan)===
In July 2019, Delcroix was sent on a one-season loan to [[Eredivisie]] club [[RKC Waalwijk]], who had just won promotion.<ref>{{cite web |title=RKC Waalwijk huurt verdediger van Anderlecht |url=https://www.rtlnieuws.nl/sport/voetbal/artikel/4778361/rkc-waalwijk-huurt-verdediger-van-anderlecht |website=RTL Nieuws |language=nl |date=12 July 2019}}</ref> On 3 August, Delcroix made his debut as a starter in the away match against [[VVV-Venlo]], scoring the opener in the eleventh minute of play. His team eventually lost the game 3–1.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Beek |first1=Yvonne van |title=RKC'er Delcroix is blij met eerste eredivisiegoal, maar baalt van resultaat |url=https://www.bd.nl/rkc-waalwijk/rkcer-delcroix-is-blij-met-eerste-eredivisiegoal-maar-baalt-van-resultaat~a3fc7be3/ |website=Brabants Dagblad |language=nl |date=3 August 2019}}</ref> Delcroix remained a starter throughout the season under head coach [[Fred Grim]]. After made a total of 24 competitive appearances, all as a starter, his loan spell ended and Delcroix returned to Anderlecht.<ref>{{cite web |title=Hannes Delcroix » Eredivisie 2019/2020 |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/person/pe427499/hannes-delcroix/ |website=WorldFootball |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |access-date=9 March 2022 |language=en}}</ref> Despite interest from RKC to extend the loan deal, Delcroix opted for a return to Anderlecht.

===Burnley===
On 22 August 2023, Delcroix joined [[Premier League]] club [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] on a three-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Verheirstraeten |first1=Michiel |title=Belofteninternational Hannes Delcroix keert terug naar Anderlecht nadat zijn club RKC Waalwijk elf (!) spelers laat gaan |url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20200512_04955882 |website=Het Nieuwsblad |language=nl-BE |date=12 May 2020}}</ref>

====Swansea City (loan)====
On 24 January 2025, Delcroix joined fellow [[EFL Championship|Championship]] club [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]] on loan for the remainder of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.swanseacity.com/news/swansea-city-complete-loan-signing-hannes-delcroix|title=Swansea City complete loan signing of Hannes Delcroix|website=www.swanseacity.com|date=24 January 2025|accessdate=24 January 2025}}</ref>

===Lugano===
On 3 January 2026, Delcroix joined [[Swiss Super League]] club [[FC Lugano|Lugano]] on a two-and-a-half-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Frusciante |first=Angelo |date=3 January 2026 |title=DAL BURNLEY ARRIVA HANNES DELCROIX |url=https://fclugano.com/en/dal-burnley-arriva-hannes-delcroix/ |access-date=9 January 2026 |website=FC Lugano |language=en-US}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Hannes share his life with long-time partner Marie-Ange Djomo, and they have a son and a daughter.

==International career==
Born in Haiti, Delcroix was raised in Belgium. He is a youth international for Belgium, and captained various of their youth teams.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hbvl.be/cnt/dmf20171108_03176154/belgie-u19-wint-ook-met-een-man-minder-makkelijk-van-liechtenstein|title=België U19 wint ook met een man minder makkelijk van Liechtenstein|date=8 November 2017 |publisher=}}</ref> He was called up to the senior [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] squad in November 2020 and made his first appearance on 11 November against Switzerland.<ref>{{cite news |title=Belgium 2–1 Switzerland|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/54892033|publisher=BBC |accessdate=11 November 2020}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] for a set of [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches in October 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haitisportuniversel.com/2025/10/03/eliminatoires-mondial-2026-hannes-delcroix-un-renfort-de-la-premier-league-pour-la-defense-haitienne/|title=Éliminatoires Mondial 2026 : Hannes Delcroix, un renfort de la Premier League pour la défense haïtienne!|first=Jean Fritzner|last=Bysson|date=3 October 2025}}</ref>

